        Ctor with necessary parameters.
        Parameters:
        token - Access token for the storage service.
        beginRequest - Parameters of the request to start the upload.
        execRequest - Parameters of the request to upload the data.
        finishRequest - Parameters of the request to finish the upload.
        destination - Destination file or folder to be moved to.
        destinationName - New name at the destination location.
        overwrite - If the destination file should be overwritten.
        data - Data stream of the uploaded file.
        size - Size of the uploaded file.
        listener - Progress listener.

      • operationBegin

        protected void operationBegin()
                       throws MultiCloudException
        Beginning of the chunked upload. If the request parameters for this method are supplied, chunked upload is started. The main purpose of this method is to obtain a session identifier for further data upload. This request uploads maximum one single chunk of data.
        Specified by:
        operationBegin in class Operation<FileInfo>
        Throws:
        MultiCloudException - If something failed.
